<!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="Content" -->
<div id="content">
  <p>To contact a <a href="http://www.rdehospital.nhs.uk/patients/wards/wards.html">ward</a>, <a href="http://www.rdehospital.nhs.uk/patients/contact/secretarynumbers.html">consultant secretary</a> or <a href="../services.html">an individual service</a>, please see  <a href="http://www.rdehospital.nhs.uk/patients/services.html">our services section</a>.   </p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p><strong>For general enquiries, please call our main hospital switchboard on   01392 411611, available 24 hours a day.</strong></p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <h2 class="patients">Your  feedback matters </h2>
  <p>Our vision is  to provide safe, high quality, seamless services   delivered with courtesy and  respect. We work hard to live up to this   and provide the highest possible  standards of care. If you have  any questions or concerns about any aspect of your   treatment or care please  talk to us about them. If you are unhappy or   unsure in any way we want to be  able to deal with your worries.</p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <div id="Accordion2">
    <h3><a href="#">How to give us positive feedback</a></h3>
    <div>
      <p class="prof">&nbsp;</p>
      <p>Our vision is  to provide safe, high quality, seamless services   delivered with courtesy and  respect. We work hard to live up to this   and provide the highest possible  standards of care. So if you have had a   good experience at the RD&amp;E then  please let us know. Telling us   what went really well can have a really  positive impact on our teams   and will ensure they carry on providing high  quality and compassionate   care every day. </p>
      <p><br />
        To send us  your positive feedback, please email <br />
  <a href="mailto:rde-tr.Positivefeedback@nhs.net">rde-tr.positivefeedback@nhs.net</a> or contact   01392 402093.      </p>
      <p>&nbsp;</p>
    </div>
<h3><a href="#">How to make a complaint</a></h3>
<div>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p class="prof">How to make a complaint </p>
  <p>We will always  work hard to resolve your concerns as quickly as   possible and to your  satisfaction. But if we cannot you may wish to   make a formal complaint. We  investigate all complaints and we will   advise you of the results of our  investigation. We aim to respond in a   positive way as your views and  experiences will help us provide a   better service for our patients and  relatives in the future.</p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p class="home">Email</p>
  <p> You can email our  Patient and Family Experience Team office on </p>
  <p><a href="mailto:rde-tr.PALS@nhs.net">rde-tr.pals@nhs.net</a>.</p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p class="prof">Phone</p>
  <p>You can call us on  01392 402093.</p>
  <p class="prof">&nbsp;</p>
  <p class="prof">By Letter</p>
  <p>Patient  Advice and Liaison   Service, Royal Devon &amp; Exeter Hospital (Wonford),  Barrack Road,   Exeter EX2 5DW. </p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p class="prof">Independent Health Complaints Advocacy </p>
  <p>If you need help making a complaint there is an independent advocacy service which offers free, impartial and confidential advice.</p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p>Telephone: 0300 343 5707 </p>
  <p>Website: <a href="http://www.seap.org.uk/services/nhs-complaints-advocacy/" target="_blank">www.seap.org.uk</a></p>
  <p>Email: <a href="mailto:info@seap.org.uk" rel="noopener" target="_blank">info@seap.org.uk</a></p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p>For more information please see our <a href="http://www.rdehospital.nhs.uk/patients/help/feedback.html">feedback section</a>.</p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<h3><a href="#">Media</a></h3>
<div>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p>All media enquiries should be directed to our Communications Team on   01392 402833 or 01392   406941 or <a href="mailto:rde-tr.RDEComms@nhs.net" target="_blank">rde-tr.rdecomms@nhs.net</a>. Outside of office hours, the on-call Press   Officer will deal with any urgent enquiries and can be contacted through   the hospital switchboard on  01392 411611, please ask for the duty manager. </p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<h3><a href="#">Work Experience </a></h3>
<div>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p>The RD&amp;E welcomes people looking for work experience  but as a   busy Acute Hospital Trust we have a duty to ensure patients receive a    high level of appropriate care so this puts some limits on the range of    opportunities we can offer. </p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p>To find out more about individual work placements please contact   our Work Experience Administrator in the Vocational Education  Team on   01392 408132.</p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p>For more information about our work experience options please see our <a href="http://www.rdehospital.nhs.uk/trust/working_for_us/work experience.html">work experience section.</a></p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<h3><a href="#">Volunteering</a></h3>
<div>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p>If you are interested in volunteering at the RD&amp;E please call 01392  402080 or email: <a href="mailto:rde-tr.volunteers@nhs.net">rde-tr.volunteers@nhs.net</a>.</p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p>For more information about our volunteer  opportunities please see our volunteers <a href="http://www.rdehospital.nhs.uk/patients/help/volunteers.html">section</a>. </p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<h3><a href="#">Accessing your medical records</a></h3>
<div>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p>The Trust’s Information Governance Team processes all such requests. You contact them by telephone on 01392 402623, or by email to <a href="mailto: rde-tr.igsupportteam@nhs.net.">rde-tr.igsupportteam@nhs.net.</a></p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p>For more information about accessing your medical records please see the information governance <a href="http://www.rdehospital.nhs.uk/trust/information-governance/accessing-information/access-your-personal-data-health-records.html">section</a>. </p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<h3><a href="#">Freedom of Information Requests (FOI)</a></h3>
<div>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p>The  Freedom of Information Act 2000 provides members of public with   the right to  request recorded information from public bodies. The Act   stipulates that you  must put your request in writing and provide us   with your name and a  correspondence address. Please be as clear and as   specific as possible  about the information you want. </p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p>You  may submit your request via email, to <a href="mailto:rde-tr.FOI@nhs.net">rde-tr.foi@nhs.net</a>,  or by post to: </p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p>Information  Governance Office<br />
    Q109<br />
    Royal  Devon and Exeter Hospital<br />
    Barrack  Road<br />
    EXETER<br />
    EX2  5DW</p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<h3><a href="#">Human Resources and <span data-hveid="110" data-ved="0ahUKEwipn8Hx55jYAhWF16QKHaQRAt4Q4EUIbjAE">Recruitment</span></a></h3>
<div>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p>For more information about Human Resources or working at the RD&amp;E please contact the HR Helpdesk: 01392 406960.</p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<h3><a href="#">General Enquiries</a></h3>
    <div>
      <p>For general enquiries,   comments and information not mentioned above please email <a href="mailto:rde-tr.WebComments@nhs.net">rde-tr.webomments@nhs.net</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <p class="patients">&nbsp;</p>
